Description: DOCGuard is a cybersecurity solution that provides fastest, in-depth file analyses and IOCs extraction. DOCGuard is located in Virginia.
Full Description: DOCGuard is a malware analysis service that performs a new kind of static analysis called structural analysis.  The structural analysis dissembles the malware and passes it to the core engines with respect to its components. With the aid of this approach, DOCGuard can precisely detect malicious documents and extract the F/P free IOCs from the documents and may also identify obfuscation and encryption in the form of string encoding and document encryption.   The detailed findings of the structural analysis are presented in an aggregated view in the GUI and can be downloaded as a JSON report and can also be gathered over API.  DOCGuard’s main use case is to integrate with SEGs (Secure Email Gateways) and SOAR solutions.

Description: Mental health app built for Organizations - integrating human-led conversation-first approach with technology to scale
Full Description: Mental health conversations that change lives. Mission - At heyy, we are on a mission to make mental health truly accessible and personal. The Why? India has more than 200 million citizens suffering from some form of mental illness. The impact of this on the economy of India is expected to be around $ 1 Trillion by 2030. The mental health topic remains tabooed and stigmatized. Or are largely unaware that they need help. Coupled with the barriers of having the least number of psychologists / therapists in India, mental health issues need an innovative solution to be tackled. The How? Despite 20,000+ apps on mental health, the issues and impact largely remains unaddressed. From habit forming products, to motivational quotes, to short content on everything from depression to anxiety, the net impact is still single digits. Then how do we tackle this problem at scale with all its complexities? The What? Let's agree - the best solution is for everyone to speak to a therapist. Period. Conversations, on this deeply human and complex challenges, with individuals who are trained. The answer lies in keeping the space personal while creating ways in which users start taking their first steps towards wellbeing.  heyy, stands out in this by not removing the human intervention for the purpose of scaling. In fact, we are deeply personal in approach, enabling conversations in an anonymous and confidential setting with our Helpers and creating a suite of products around it, to nudge, help, plan and get our users better. On our app, users get access to - 1. Self Assessments - Tangible measures to assess mental health and wellbeing 2. Lifebuoys - Bite-sized and research backed resources, to inform and nudge 3. Helpers - 24x7 mental health first-aid, by trained psychologists 4. Experts - For intensive therapy needs It just takes a heyy, ! Get started today.

Industry Groups: Health Care

Description: Recommerce platform - E-commerce, SaaS and on-demand buyback of consumer electronics
Full Description: reboxed isn’t your average recommerce company. We are a combination of technology, branding, and environmental impact - an on-demand platform for businesses and people to sell, swap and shop for used tech because we believe great tech shouldn't cost the Earth. Our obsession with having the latest smartphone the second it drops is creating mountains of e-waste. Why? One, it's too much hassle to sell. Two, refurbished phones have a bad rep. Until now.  We refurbish and rebox used devices into premium phones - making it easier, faster, and more trustworthy. So fewer perfectly good phones go to waste. And one by one, we can save millions more from landfill. Our circular business model – rebox, rehome, repeat – isn’t just designed to give our customers better value, but make a positive impact on the environment and society.  We don’t just reward people for reboxing. We reward the planet by planting 10 trees every time we buy or sell a device and paying to offset each phone’s lifetime CO2 emissions, which helps to fund a whole range of projects to cut CO2. Our goal is to try and make every phone we rehome not just carbon neutral, but carbon positive if we can. We've come to shake up a dated and boring category. To solve inefficiencies. To redefine recommerce. To challenge the status quo. To liberate people from their addiction to linear, and create a circular economy that rewards them for making greener choices and helping to replenish the planet. One device at a time. We’re on a mission to 100 million phones by 2030. And transform the way people buy, sell, and think about tech. We are reboxed. Recommerce, on-demand
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Consumer Electronics, Hardware

Description: Anuncia Medical is a CSF Management startup with an FDA Breakthrough Device platform to prevent shunt failure and revision brain surgery.
Full Description: Anuncia Medical is an early-stage commercial, patient-centric MedTech company with the US cleared and EU-approved, clinically validated, noninvasive, therapeutic device solutions and a robust product pipeline to disrupt the Cerebrospinal Fluid (CSF) Management space. We uniquely address the largest unmet need in CSF Management; the high rate of ventriculoperitoneal (VP) shunt occlusion. VP shunts fail at a rate of 50% within 2 years and 80% within 5 years, contributing to repeat revision brain surgeries (each costing upwards of $40,000).  Conceptualized in 2014 in collaboration with Boston Children’s Hospital and spun out of Alcyone Therapeutics in 2018, Anuncia’s patented portfolio of technologies provide peace-of-mind through innovation to improve daily quality of life for the millions of underserved patients with hydrocephalus and other CSF disorders and their families, who suffer from the clinical, economic, and emotional burden of repeat revision brain surgery due to VP shunt occlusions. Anuncia’s core platform has an elegant mechanism of action using a simple finger depression of a soft silicone dome located under the patient’s scalp to produce a noninvasive, retrograde flush of the patient’s own CSF to restore flow through an occluded catheter and prevent emergency surgery. ReFlow’s initial clinical evidence of flow restoration and reduction of symptoms via acute intervention flushing with follow-up up to 3 years, led neurosurgeons to evaluate ReFlow for prophylactic occlusion prevention in their high-risk patients. Ground-breaking clinical data, now out up to 2 years with 100% success, suggest ReFlow is safe for at-home, prophylactic flushing by patients or caregivers to extend shunt life and eliminate revision brain surgery. Supported by these encouraging results, the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) granted ReFlow Breakthrough Device status in 2021, making it eligible for regulatory and reimbursement advantages. With existing profitable reimbursement, Anuncia plans to launch its next-generation ReFlow Mini product line in Q2 2022 and continue clinical studies to support market adoption and premium reimbursement.  With Breakthrough status and strong health economic advantages to improve hospital quality metrics and support New Technology Add-on Payment (NTAP) for rapid market adoption and premium pricing; Anuncia is positioned to be the leader in CSF management and help patients live fuller lives.  ReFlow’s unique ability to improve patient access to noninvasive lifesaving therapy at home or in the clinic and to improve clinical outcomes and quality of life, and reduce healthcare costs, earned it an Honorable Mention in the Fast Company 2021 World-Changing Ideas Awards and landed it on MDDI’s The Ultimate List of Private Companies to Watch.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Description: GOI is an experience focused logistics operator that provides solutions for bulky item deliveries in urban areas
Full Description: GOI Travel GOI is a bulky shipping logistics startup that operates on the last mile at the province level, where logistics operators do not have specific services for bulky products, especially furniture and appliances. Its platform has managed to order a sector hitherto atomized and with a lot of intrusions since, thanks to technology, it connects autonomous carriers with users, optimizing and lowering the service. Traditionally, companies that wanted to make bulky shipments had to hire the services of autonomous carriers or moving companies or, failing that, have their own truck or delivery van. GOI breaks with this archaic freight transport system by providing autonomous carriers of technology and giving them volume, reducing that 40% of the time they spent searching for their customers. Description: Uila gives collaborative solution that effectively visualizes and automatically correlates application performance to virtual.
Full Description: Data center architecture has evolved dramatically in recent years, enabling it to effectively run large-scale, distributed, multi-tier applications across public, private and hybrid cloud environments. To support and ultimately ensure delivery of business-critical applications and services, a distinct architecture has emerged. This complex structure involves dynamic resource sharing over a hyper-converged compute, storage and network physical infrastructure, all supported by a layer of virtualization technologies. This new, integrated approach to data center architecture offers tremendous operational and business advantages to organizations whose success is dependent upon reliable application service delivery. However, data center monitoring solutions and technology developments have not kept pace with this new wave in data center architecture. Current tools have reinforced the established silos that separate applications, virtual infrastructure, and physical infrastructure as well as the supporting IT teams within the data center. As a result, data center teams have no inter-silo visibility and are unable to efficiently connect the dots between infrastructure and application performance. Uila has a transformational vision that addresses this problem, and empowers data center infrastructure and application teams with a revolutionary new collaborative solution that effectively visualizes and automatically correlates application performance to virtual and physical infrastructure root cause. Monitoring application and IT infrastructure in a virtualized data center calls for an equally virtualized monitoring architecture. The Uila vision completely transforms data center monitoring with a game-changing approach that leverages virtualization technology. The advanced Uila solution delivers faster and more accurate identification of application performance root cause, provides effective remediation, and prevents future performance degradation…while reducing IT total cost of ownership.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Industry Groups: Hardware, Information Technology, Software
Founders: Chia Chee Kuan, Dean Au, Miles Wu

And as powerful as coaching continually proves to be, it only accounts for less than 5% of sales managers time. So,to make sales coaching simple, more time efficient and to amplify the benefits, we built Refract. By highlighting the decisive and defining moments of these conversations and surfacing coachable insight specific to your business and reps, mistakes and missed opportunities can be remedied. Our AI technology delivers personalized insight, based on your business and your reps, showing the actions and words that align with top performers and results. They combine their powerful insights and rigorous scientific methods to help pharmaceutical companies overcome the obstacle of the blood-brain barrier.

Description: Ukrainian product IT company that develops an ecosystem of services for effective management of business, its resources and processes.
Full Description: According to the Startup Genome Report research today, 97% of companies do not live more than 3 years due to an inefficient combination of resources in the implementation of basic needs and management of project activities. Vymex is the first company in the world that is developing a resource that will allow users to effectively isolate the management of a company's basic needs into a single ecosystem. Basic needs are configured by ALL companies, and they do this by combining different software and tools (messengers, tables, documents, etc.). When scaling up, companies often integrate different ERP systems that combine tools to manage baseline needs and project activities. The Vymex application structure includes 4 products that perform all these functions easily. vHub - it includes functionality for creating and managing a company in a mobile app. Just create a structure and add other users to it. vCo-f - a product that helps you properly to own your share in the company, to keep track of development progress, make decisions by the entire membership of the co-founders and to add new ones by selling your share. vChat - messenger for communication within the ecosystem. Separates business communication from personal. Secure data encryption, fast download and file transfer speeds. vRise - A tool for creating CVs and job searches within the ecosystem. In the first commercial year, Vymex can be used by small companies of up to 50 people. Location and niche do not matter. Companies will pay for subscriptions depending on the size and number of structural units. This will be much more efficient than the current business management methods. The product system and the company design everything so that it sells subscriptions immediately to the global market. Released Beta application on IOS and Android. Now there are open tests by users (more than 500) and companies (more than 250). We also developed our own encryption protocol, which is used to implement the entire software architecture, which allows us to create a quality competition on the global market. We spent 14 out of the planned 19 months in active development. We estimated the intellectual property at 14.5 million hryvnias. There are 46 people on the team at the time of beta release. Round A is designed to attract private investment to develop a commercial version of products. This minimizes the risks for investors at an early stage and allows them to easily manage their assets in the future. Today, 0.1 to 10% of the company is for sale. Proposals for funds will be available after the release of the commercial version. We will develop the necessary legal structure and prepare the product to meet the planned results before the release of the commercial version. Project calculations are constantly being refined and developed. The company will start making a profit in 2024. The business model and products allow us to scale the company to a capitalization of $1.8 billion by 2030. Capitalization will start to grow as soon as we reorganize the company into a JSC and conduct the first round of funds. This will significantly increase the company's performance and provide funds to scale the model to the global market.

Description: Vena Medical creating a forward viewing imaging microcatheter that allows physicians to see inside patient blood vessels.
Full Description: Vena Medical has created the Vena Microcatheter in order to provide physicians with a view inside blood vessels. This microcatheter uses bleeding edge fiberoptics and a saline flush in order to give physicians a point of view of their tools. We're even working on a second generation that uses infrared light to eliminate the saline flush. This will greatly improve vascular navigation during minimally invasive procedures. This tool would replace traditional catheters and would provide a first-person navigational perspective for physicians, allowing them to inspect their work once they're done. This new perspective would make procedures faster by eliminating the iterative nature of navigation and safer by reducing guidewire induced punctures of arteries and veins. The harmless visible light would reduce the quantity of fluoroscopy and iodine required for these procedures. Patients, physicians and nurses would all be subjected to less radiation while simultaneously increasing the size of the candidate pool for these interventional procedures.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

ARU (Asura Recognition Unit) license plate recognition and traffic data collection software (existing product): licensed per server, license fee is based on volume. License fee consists of two parts: (1) upfront fee, paid in lump sum, granting lifetime license, (2) update fee (10% of upfront license fee), paid yearly from 2nd year. Description: Frontity is a free and open source framework for building headless WordPress sites using React.
Full Description: We have been crafting open source software for WordPress for many years now but the whole idea of this project came up in late 2017, when we started working with big Spanish WordPress publishers who wanted to improve the performance of their mobile sites. Despite their best efforts, their WordPress sites on mobile devices were slow and sluggish. We got down to work and developed a mobile WordPress theme for them, called Frontity PRO. Our goal: to make it as performant as possible while delivering a remarkable user experience. To achieve that, we built an internal React framework which used the REST API to fetch the content of their WordPress sites, and spent the whole year optimizing it. We faced a lot of challenges and realized that combining WordPress and React wasn’t easy. But at the end, the theme was a success: it was used by more than 20 million readers and proven ideal for building engaging and modern frontend experiences. In 2019 we decided to use all that knowledge and lessons learnt to launch an open source framework, so anyone who wants to use WordPress as a headless CMS with a React frontend could benefit. We believe that WordPress and React are destined to live together and are committed to helping it happen.
Headquarters Regions: European Union (EU), Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)

Full Description: Witseed is an Edtech formed by a team of passionate about education, technology and cinema, and we aim to reinvent the education experience to help professionals and companies reach their goals. Our focus is to produce quality content connected to the market and made available in our adaptive learning platform, which personalizes the learning experience. Witseed's great differential was to reverse the logic of the market, and instead of creating content and going to market to get customers, we created a board with the largest companies in Brazil to curate and validate all content to be produced. Each company that believed in the model, one executive indicated to attend the Board of Education, which was structured with follow-up routines to validate the topics that most interested the companies and have greater impact on the challenges that they are going through. Witseed was born in July 2017, with the following clients: Algar, Braskem, BrasilFoods, Sabesp, Siemens, Fiat, Calcenter Group, Saint-Gobain, Oncoclinics, GRSA, Gerdau, CCR, Natura, Grupo Pão de Açúcar, Random, Ecorodovias and FIERGS. This model resulted in a different monetization strategy, since the companies paid development quotas before the product actually existed, and after having a number of companies in the Board, we started the project. It ended up being a funding in the bootstrapping model, with investment coming directly from our customers, through the revenue sold to them: we opened that the investment to create a niche academy, with thematic content, which in this case was the SSAcademy (Shared Services Academy), was almost 1 million, and to that end, we would form a board of companies, which would divide this amount into equal quotas, thus becoming customers of Witseed. As a benefit, they would pay less to gain access to all developed content and would also participate in a Board of Education, curating all content that was to be developed. SSAcademy's first wave of content was delivered two months ago, and companies are already using, with very positive feedbacks. As an indicator of success, we have after 2 months of launching the first version with our content, about 6,000 professionals in the platform, with a satisfaction rating of 4.76 (on a scale of 1 to 5) as well as having several statements from the Directors and Managers who are our clients, as a case of success and innovation in Corporate Education, from being prominent for the agile development of high quality content, even by participating in the innovation of Content Co-construction between companies. Description: Liopa’s LipRead deciphers speech from lip movements. It uses AI and deep learning for automated lip reading.
Full Description: We are Liopa. We were incorporated in 2015 to commercialise more than 15 years of PhD research at QUB in the field of speech and image processing. Using this deep knowledge, we developed an automated lipreading solution. Our technology – rooted in machine learning and AI – can decipher what a person is saying from their lip movements alone. Liopa is the first company to release commercially available VSR (Visual Speech Recognition) technology, with the first application being our SRAVI app (www.sravi.ai).  SRAVI is a simple lipreading application that requires just a smartphone. It is bringing a voice to the voiceless.  With SRAVI, we help patients who have lost the ability to speak, to communicate with their loved ones & carers. SRAVI is deployed onto a smartphone, and when pointed towards the patient, the app analyses their lip movements to decipher what they are trying to say.  SRAVI is being trialled in Intensive Care units within the NHS.

Spent grain is the number one byproduct from breweries and for over 100 years, breweries have been trying to develop a way to capitalize on this resource--think whey protein from cheese making. Our innovative methodology allows us to dry and mill brewers spent grain in under 20 minutes, down from the conventional 6 hours--allowing us to provide this incredibly healthy and sustainable ingredient at affordable prices to consumers and product makers. Since launching 10 months ago, we have been able to upcycle 120,000 lbs of wet spent grain, and have launched 2 CPG products in nearly 200 HEB stores. We are now in the works of developing contracts with product makers, bakeries, and even a dog food company!
